-- AFRICA WEEK AHEAD: African Union Summit, Nigeria June Inflation
-- B y   B r y s o n   H u l l
-- 2012-07-16T06:30:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/africa-week-ahead-african-union-summit-nigeria-june-inflation.html
The  African Union  finishes its 19th
summit in  Addis Ababa , the Ethiopian capital, today after
electing South African Home Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini- Zuma head of the continental body’s commission.  Nigeria is scheduled to release June inflation data on July
18, after May’s rate fell to 12.7 percent.  Tanzania publishes June inflation data today. The rate
declined for a fifth month in May to 18.2 percent, the National
Bureau of Statistics said on June 15. 